This test currently uses `Recursive(42, Nil)`, which would also encode as `[]` with the default derived codec. As a result, it doesn't actually prove the type+term-name instance override is being applied. Consider asserting encoding for a non-empty `ln` (e.g., via an `encode(...)`-style assertion rather than `roundTrip`) so the test fails if the override is ignored.
```suggestion
        // ln field always encodes as empty array regardless of content;
        // use a non-empty list to ensure the custom codec override is applied
        encode(
          Recursive(42, List(Recursive(1, Nil))),
          """{"i":42,"ln":[]}""",
          codec
