`printVariant` no longer has a compact rendering for variants with no cases. With `cases.isEmpty` the current output becomes `variant X {\n}` (multiline) rather than `variant X {}` like before, which is inconsistent with empty records and will change pretty-printed SDL for empty variants. Consider adding an early return for `variant.cases.isEmpty` to preserve the single-line `{}` form.
```suggestion
    sb.append("variant ").append(sdlTypeName(variant.typeId))
    if (variant.cases.isEmpty) {
      sb.append(" {}").toString
    } else {
      sb.append(" {\n")
      variant.cases.foreach { case_ =>
        sb.append(printVariantCase(case_, indent + 1, visited)).append('\n')
      }
      indentString(sb, indent)
      sb.append('}').toString
    }
```

`printRecord` always appends `indentString(sb, indent)` before `}` even when `record.fields` is empty. When a nested empty record is printed with `indent > 0`, this introduces extra spaces inside the braces (e.g. `record X {  }`). Consider special-casing `record.fields.isEmpty` to return `record <Type> {}` without inserting indentation, matching the previous output and avoiding formatting artifacts.
```suggestion
    if (record.fields.isEmpty) {
      sb.append('}').toString
    } else {
      record.fields.foreach {
        var isFirst = true
        field =>
          if (isFirst) {
            sb.append('\n')
            isFirst = false
          }
          indentString(sb, indent + 1)
          sb.append(printTerm(field, indent + 1, visited)).append('\n')
      }
      indentString(sb, indent)
      sb.append('}').toString
    }
```

