Using asInstanceOf to cast the result of toList to :: is unsafe. If the chunk happens to be empty (which should not happen for NonEmptyChunk but could if there's a bug), toList will return Nil, and the cast will fail at runtime with a ClassCastException. The previous implementation was safer by constructing the :: explicitly. Consider either keeping the previous safer implementation or adding an assertion to document that the chunk must be non-empty.
```suggestion
  def toCons[A1 >: A]: ::[A1] =
    chunk.toList match {
      case cons @ (_ :: _) => cons
      case Nil              =>
        throw new IllegalStateException("NonEmptyChunk.toCons: underlying chunk was empty")
    }
```

