`leak` expands to `$scopedExpr.run()`, but `run()` is `private[scope]` on `Scoped`. Macro expansions are typechecked at the call site, so calling `leak(...)` from code outside the `zio.blocks.scope` package is likely to fail with an access error. Consider implementing `leak` via a publicly accessible unsafe-unwrapping entry point (e.g., a public `@@.unsafeUnwrap`/`Scoped.unsafeRun` used by the macro) or otherwise ensuring the expanded code does not reference package-private members.
```suggestion
