This falls back to `Schema.derived[T]` for *any* implicit search failure, including ambiguous/diverging implicit errors. That can mask real configuration problems (e.g., multiple `Schema[T]` in scope) and silently change behavior. Recommendation: only auto-derive when the failure is truly ‘not found’, and otherwise surface the compiler’s implicit-search failure (e.g., abort with the failure explanation).
```suggestion
      case failure: ImplicitSearchFailure =>
        failure match {
          case _: ImplicitSearchFailure.NoMatchingImplicits =>
            // No Schema[T] in scope, fall back to automatic derivation
            '{ Schema.derived[T] }
          case _ =>
